The paper is about a novel sequence-to-sequence schema for dependency parsing, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses Pointer Networks, which are a type of neural network, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions logistic regression, which is a common technique in machine learning, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) since some NLP tasks, such as named entity recognition, involve analyzing images of text.
